                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d662">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">825.30 Missions/12–1544: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-12-15T21:00:00-04:00"
                            >December 15, 1944—9 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 11:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1930. Fernández expresses greatest satisfaction over our willingness to send a
                    naval mission to Chile and the President expresses satisfaction with the
                    proposal to send first a Rear Admiral here to make a survey to determine amount
                    of personnel, et cetera. A formal request for the mission will be conveyed to
                    the Department by Ambassador Mora.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bowers</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
